<p><hr size=2 color="black">

<a name="khan"></a>
<center><table cellpadding=5><tr><td>
<img src="thumb/Khan_thumbnail.jpg" alt="Khan" width=93 height=117>
<td>
<h2>Khan, Kublai<br>(1215 - 1294)</h2>
</td></tr></table></center>

<p> Kublai Khan was a Mongol leader who according to Marco Polo maintained some 5000 court astrologers, whose duties included the hazardous task of weather prediction. Why so many? Guessing wrong, he explained, could lead to "early retirement".

